{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620665","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620665"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:46:35+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:46:35+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16645"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16645","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16645"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.91,0,0.05,0.03]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9336"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66115"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9336","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9336"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16645"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51572"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5029"},{"type":"tags","id":"8412"},{"type":"tags","id":"9882"},{"type":"tags","id":"10104"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22113"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22118"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66115","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66115"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EGlyceryl trinitrate is commonly used in the treatment of angina and acute coronary syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the primary mechanism of action of glyceryl trinitrate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inhibition of angiotensin converting enzyme","Conversion to nitric oxide leading to smooth muscle relaxation","Reduces sympathetic outflow from the central nervous system","Blocks calcium channels in vascular smooth muscle","Direct stimulation of beta-2 adrenergic receptors"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe primary mechanism of action of glyceryl trinitrate involves its \u003Cstrong\u003Econversion to nitric oxide leading to smooth muscle relaxation\u003C/strong\u003E. Nitric oxide activates guanylate cyclase, increasing cyclic guanosine monophosphate (cGMP) levels in vascular smooth muscle cells. This leads to vasodilation of both veins and arteries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibition of angiotensin converting enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E represents the mechanism of ACE inhibitors like enalapril, which reduce blood pressure by preventing the formation of angiotensin II. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReducing sympathetic outflow from the central nervous system\u003C/strong\u003E is how centrally-acting antihypertensives like clonidine work to lower blood pressure. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocking calcium channels in vascular smooth muscle\u003C/strong\u003E describes the mechanism of calcium channel blockers like nifedipine, which causes vasodilation by preventing calcium entry into smooth muscle cells. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirect stimulation of beta-2 adrenergic receptors\u003C/strong\u003E is the mechanism of beta agonists like salbutamol, which causes bronchodilation and vascular smooth muscle relaxation through a different pathway.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe vasodilatory effects of glyceryl trinitrate, particularly venodilation, reduce cardiac preload and myocardial oxygen demand, making it useful in treating angina and acute coronary syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Glyceryl trinitrate is converted to nitric oxide which causes smooth muscle relaxation via increased cyclic guanosine monophosphate.","The primary therapeutic effect of glyceryl trinitrate is vasodilation of veins and arteries.","Glyceryl trinitrate reduces cardiac preload by causing venous pooling of blood."],"references":["Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51572"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16645"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51572","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51572"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-29T11:57:15+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-04T09:30:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9336"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66115"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relation